{
  "stem": "12255.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These were reported to us mainly in the Jewish press, the We knew about that, and we knew about Kristallnacht, but we certainly did not know-- did not understand, and hardly could comprehend-- what was going on in the concentration camps and how Jews were being slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I-- I don't think many people knew, outside, maybe, some of the leadership in London.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But many people did not really understand this until the news reels began, on-- particularly the news reels about Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I doubt it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Were not known, generally.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went straight into the chaplaincy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's called a chaplaincy corps, and I was stationed at the-- at a place called Colchester, which was the largest intake center for new recruits being brought in from the whole of the London-- of the southern England area.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at any one time, there were many, many thousands of boys coming there for the-- what you call square bashing, after which they were posted to various units.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the basic training camp, and I established a little synagogue on the camp, and we had very-- very-- a very nice arrangement where the boys were free, particularly on Friday night-- sometimes on Saturdays-- and we used to get good gatherings from the recruits who were only too glad to be able to see something of Jewishness, like they were experiencing in their own home.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fair.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, everybody had to go, so there was quite a large intake, per capita, of Jewish boys.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, and particularly in London.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not the faintest idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, as-- as I said, I was stationed in Colchester.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
